

### INSTRUCTIONS

1. Clone the repository
2. Run the following command to install the required packages:
```bash
npm install
```
3. Run the following command to start the server:
```bash
npm start
```
4. If you want to add covers to the books, you can use the following command:
```bash
npm run books:add-covers
```

### API ENDPOINTS
1. GET /api/v1/books
2. GET /api/v1/books/:id
3. POST /api/v1/books
4. PUT /api/v1/books/:id
5. DELETE /api/v1/books/:id
6. GET /api/v1/authors
7. GET /api/v1/authors/:id
8. POST /api/v1/authors
9. PUT /api/v1/authors/:id
10. DELETE /api/v1/authors/:id

For postman collection, please refer to file: `Library.postman_collection.json` in the root directory.
